- "last 30 days" refers to the time period from the current date to 30 days ago; 
- The temperatures are assumed to be averaged over all readings for each facility within this time frame; 
- The ordering is based on the average temperature, with the facility having the highest average temperature appearing first.

- The term "last year" refers to the 12 months preceding the current date; 
- "maintenance counts" imply the number of maintenance activities performed; 
- "average sensor quality scores" indicate the mean quality of data collected by sensors within each facility.

sql:
SELECT facility_type_name, description
FROM facility_types
ORDER BY facility_type_name;
